<item>
            <title>[LU-5045] OFED is only available on https now</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5045</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+ wget -nv http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//OFED-1.5.4.tgz -O /var/lib/jenkins/lbuild-data/kerneltree/OFED-1.5.4.tgz
http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//OFED-1.5.4.tgz:
2014-05-09 19:44:52 ERROR 400: Bad Request.
+ rc=1
+ return 1
+ fatal 1 &apos;Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.&apos;
+ cleanup
+ true
+ error &apos;Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.&apos;
+ local &apos;msg=Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.&apos;
+ &apos;[&apos; -n &apos;Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.&apos; &apos;]&apos;
+ echo -e &apos;\nlbuild: Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.&apos;

lbuild: Could not download OFED-1.5.4.tgz from http://www.openfabrics.org/downloads/OFED/ofed-1.5.4//.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because the OFED download site is only available on https now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While old builders, that have a copy of OFED cached from when the download site didn&apos;t require https this change breaks builds on new builders which need to fetch a copy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
